column1: OMAP-17: Organ Mapping Antibody Panel (OMAP) for Multiplexed Antibody-Based Imaging of Thymus with IBEX

column2: Andrea J. Radtke; Brianna T. Wachter; Rebecca T. Beuschel; Nadav Yayon; Veronika Kedlian; Lena Boehme; Ronald Germain; Luigi Notarangelo; Marita Bosticardo; Francesca Pala; Sarah Teichmann; Tom Taghon

column24: rationale

This antibody defines developing cytotoxic T cells in the medulla and cortex. This marker represents a core marker and prioritized target in the thymus OMAP. Note: Antibody detects CD8alpha and not CD8beta expressing T cells.
This marker can be used to distinguish neuro-endocrine thymic epithelial cells (TECs) in the medulla. This is a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
This marker is expressed by macrophages at the corticomedullary boundary and along the trabeculae. This is a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.

This antibody defines T cells in the medulla and cortex. HIgher expression of CD3 by medullary T cells can distinguish the medulla from the cortex. This marker represents a core marker and prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
CD99 is expressed by granulocytes and eosinophils. This marker is not a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Used to detect CD99.
This antibody cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure but targets an essential marker for dendritic cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Used to detect CD11c.
Essential marker of B cells. B cells are enriched in the medulla of the thymus. This marker represents a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Critical marker for defining developing thymocytes along with CD5 and CD34. This marker represents a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Defines blood endothelial cells and vessels of thymus. Critical marker for defining developing thymocytes along with CD5 and CD7. This marker represents a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Critical marker for defining developing thymocytes along with CD7 and CD34. This marker represents a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
This marker defines the vasculature of the thymus and targets an essential marker for blood endothelial cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.

This marker does not define a specific anatomical structure but is expressed by subsets of T regulatory cells, mesenchymal cells, and endothelial cells of the thymus. This marker is not a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Defines nerves and neuro thymic epithelial cells (TECs). This marker is a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.

Antibody recognizes the Vα7.2 T cell antigen receptor (TCR) α-chain segment, enabling detection of mucosal-associated invariant T cells (MAIT cells). This marker is not a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
This antibody defines developing helper T cells in the medulla and cortex. This marker represents a core marker and prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
This antibody cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure. However, it targets an essential marker for T regulatory cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Labels the nuclear membrane of thymic epithelial cells (TECs) and can be used with Hoechst to empower segmentation of TEC populations. This marker is not a prioritized target for the thymus OMAP.
Essential marker for plasmacytoid dendritic cells and additionally labels some fibroblasts and endothelial cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.

HLA-DR is an essential marker for antigen presenting cells (B cells, dendritic cells, macrophages) and thymic epithelial cells (TECs) found throughout the thymus. Higher expression of HLA-DR on medullary TECs can be used to define the medulla. This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Essential marker for cortical macrophages. This marker represents a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Antibody labels macrophages, endothelial cells, and stromal populations including thymic epithelial cells (TECs). This marker is not a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Used to detect SPARC.
This marker can be used to distinguish myo thymic epithelial cells (TECs) in the medulla as well as smooth muscle cells and myofibroblasts. This is a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Critical marker for cortical thymic epithelial cells (TECs). Defines the cortex. This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Used to detect LY75.

Critical transcription factor for thymic epithelial cells (TECs) in the medulla. However, antibody performance is highly variable. This marker is a prioritized target for the thymus OMAP but better antibodies are needed.
Labels endothelial cells and small populations of thymic epithelial cells (TECs) in the medulla. This marker is not a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Essential marker for dividing thymocytes that can be used to distinguish the cortex (Ki-67++) from the medulla (Ki-67+/-). This is a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Key marker for immature thymic epithelial cells (TECs) with KRT14 and KRT15. This marker is also expressed by populations of mesenchymal cells. This is a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.

Labels lymphatic endothelial cells and efferent lymphatic vessels of the thymus. Lymphatic vessels are very hard to find in thin tissue sections of the thymus. This is not a prioritized target for the thymus OMAP.
Expressed by mTECIII  cells enriched in Hassall’s corpuscles. This marker critically defines Hassall’s corpuscles and represents a prioritized target for the thymus OMAP.

Defines trabeculae and thymus capsule, providing an outline of the functional tissue unit of the thymic loboule. Lumican is also enriched around the corticomedullary boundary. This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target in the healthy thymus OMAP.
This marker labels mesenchymal cells, smooth muscle cells, NK cells, and activated T cells. This marker is not a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
This marker is expressed by subsets of thymic epithelial cells (TECs) in the medulla (mTEC). This is a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Used to detect KRT15.
This marker is expressed by eosinophils, granulocytes, and extravasated neutrophils. This is a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Defines stromal network of thymus medulla and serves as a pan-mesenchymal cell marker. This marker represents a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Expressed by mTEC populations at varying levels. This marker represents a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Defines granulocytes and monocytes. This marker represents a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Essential marker for gamma delta T cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.

This marker cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure but is expressed by all hematopoietic cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP and can be used for downstream image analysis.

Neuroendocrine marker expressed by thymic epithelial cells in the medulla in a sex-specific manner (higher in females?). Follow up studies needed. This marker is not a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Used to detect SYP.

column3: HGNC:6413, HGNC:6416, HGNC:6421, HGNC:6423, HGNC:6436, HGNC:6412, HGNC:6439, HGNC:6440, HGNC:6441, HGNC:6442, HGNC:6445, HGNC:6446
column4: KRT10, KRT14, KRT15, KRT16, KRT19, KRT1, KRT2, KRT3, KRT4, KRT5, KRT7, KRT8
column24: Pan-cytokeratin marker labels epithelial cells throughout the thymus. This marker represents a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Expressed by thymic epithelial cells (TECs) populations at varying levels. This marker represents a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Expressed by reticular cells and smooth muscle cells of the thymus. This marker represents a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
Expressed by thymic epithelial cells (TECs) populations at varying levels. This marker represents a prioritized target in the thymus OMAP.
